  },
  "instructions_to_main_agent": [
    "Build standard React Native Expo functional components in .js files.",
    "Use StyleSheet.create for styling to apply the design guidelines provided above.",
    "Follow the mobile-first (Android) requirement strictly using SafeAreaView where appropriate.",
    "Ensure generous whitespace by using spacing.xl or spacing.xxl between main sections.",
    "Implement the 'Start a Case' flow with clear step indicators (e.g., 3 progress dots).",
    "For icons (mic, clock, profile, back arrow), use @expo/vector-icons like Feather or Ionicons.",
    "No drop shadows should be used unless extremely subtle; rely primarily on borders and layout.",
    "For the mirror confirmation screen, render AI text in italic within the CardMirror style.",
    "Use ScrollView or KeyboardAvoidingView for screens containing text inputs.",
    "The verdict screen should use BadgeSuccess or BadgeWarning depending on the outcome.",
    "All interactive and key informational elements MUST include a data-testid attribute for robust automated testing."
  ]
}